Hi,<br><br><em class="text-italics">I'm currently developing games with LÖVE, which implies developing tools when I don't find a suitable one and I like to make them generic (not bound to a specific thing). This post is one among others in the future to share those Lua librairies which may interest LÖVE developers.</em><br><br>Luaoop is an Object Oriented Programming (class-based) library. There are many of those, but I didn't find something as clean as I wanted and it was interesting to make.<br><br>Project and documentation: <a href="https://github.com/ImagicTheCat/Luaoop" class="postlink">https://github.com/ImagicTheCat/Luaoop</a><br><br>If you are interested by how it looks in a project using the library, here is an <a href="https://github.com/ImagicTheCat/vRP/blob/master/vrp/vRPShared.lua" class="postlink">example</a> unrelated to LÖVE.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="https://love2d.org/forums/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=143604">Imagic</a> — Wed Feb 05, 2020 6:41 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
